<html><head><meta http-equiv="Content-Type" content="text/html; charset=utf-8" /><meta http-equiv="Content-Style-Type" content="text/css" /><meta name="generator" content="Aspose.Words for .NET 13.4.0.0" /><title>Written evidence from David Bridge (CYS0081)</title></head><body><div><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:center"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">Written evidence from </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">David Bridge</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> (CYS0081)</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">Thank you for your invitation to send in my views on cycling safety. These are my views. Whether this makes it evidence I don't know.</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">1. Is Cycling, especially urban cycling safe</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">Nothing totally safe in the real world. In fact urban cycling is safer on a</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> per mile basis than rural cycling. I am told that cycling is about as safe per mile as being a pedestrian; </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">We</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> just worry about cycling more. As it puts up your life expectancy it can't be that dangerous. 69 or so pedestrians were killed in London last yea</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">r. Has any fuss been made about that? Most of those who call cycling too dangerous seem just to want cyclists off the roads.</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">One oft-forgotten issue is that cycling along rural </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">A</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> roads is particularly dangerous. Some thought should be given to installing </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">cycle-ways on these whenever building new ones. Here at least there are few pedestrians to clash with.</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">2</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold"> What central and local Government could </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">do</span></p><ol type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 32pt; padding-left:4pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">Accidents that cause death on the roads should be treated as seriously as accidents that cause death anywhe</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">re else.</span></li><li style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 32pt; padding-left:4pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">The law about mobile phone use while driving should be much more widely enforced.</span></li><li style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 32pt; padding-left:4pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">There is no such thing as an attention-free phone, so ban hands-free phones too.</span></li><li style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 32pt; padding-left:4pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">The police should be obliged to check the mobile phone records </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">of  the</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> driver who is</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> involved in any accident that causes injury to any road user.</span></li><li style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 32pt; padding-left:4pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">Accidents involving commercial vehicles while engaged in commercial activity should be recorded as “Accidents at work”.</span></li><li style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 32pt; padding-left:4pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">HGV drivers should be monitored properly so that that do not exceed their</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> permitted driving hours. A tired driver is a dangerous driver.</span></li><li style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 32pt; padding-left:4pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">HGV drivers should be required to pass regular, accredited eye checks.</span></li><li style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 32pt; padding-left:4pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">Random breath testing should be permitted.</span></li><li style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 32pt; padding-left:4pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">Don't allow longer lorries</span></li><li style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">Don't raise the permitted speed of </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">lorries</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> on singl</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">e carriageway A roads.</span></li><li style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">Help converting existing unused routes such as disused railways and canal paths into </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">cycleways</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">.</span></li></ol><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">3.</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold"> Whether it would be desirable and feasible to segregate cyclists from other road users, including, for example, by prohibiting HGVs f</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">rom entering city centres at peak hours</span></p><ol type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 32pt; padding-left:4pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">The postulated "London Skyways" might help. There are probably cheaper places to start.</span></li><li style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 32pt; padding-left:4pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">Fit pedestrian &amp; cycle flyovers over notorious roundabouts.</span></li><li style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 32pt; padding-left:4pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">Traffic schemes should treat cyclists and pedestrians as a normal pa</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">rt of road traffic not an unwanted add-on. They should be designed so that pedestrians and cyclists would want to use them. Sets of crossing lights that take about 10 minutes to cross a road are not </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">acceptable</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">.</span></li><li style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 32pt; padding-left:4pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">Shared cycle/pedestrian ways are a really bad</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> idea. Pedestrians and cyclists don't mix. I once saw a note saying "Cycling on the pavement is more dangerous than cycling in the road. And it's illegal. So don't do it". It's probably right. Pedestrians do not have eyes in the back of their heads and fre</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">quently do not stick to their half of the shared path. They never will. A 1metre wide cycle lane in the road is a much better idea. Two possible exceptions are </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">are</span></li><ol type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 50pt; padding-left:4pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">Shared cycle/pedestrian flyovers.</span></li><li style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 50pt; padding-left:4pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">Out of town where there are few pedestrians.</span></li></ol><li style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 32pt; padding-left:4pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">Cycleways</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> are</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> also not popular with cyclists because:</span></li><ol type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 50pt; padding-left:4pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">They are often littered with glass. Car tyres crush glass, cycle tyres get punctures.</span></li><li style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 50pt; padding-left:4pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">You are always stopping and starting at junctions</span></li><li style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 50pt; padding-left:4pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">It's quicker in the road</span></li></ol><li style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 32pt; padding-left:4pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">Cycle lanes in roadways should be a minimum of 1 metre</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> wide.</span></li><li style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 32pt; padding-left:4pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">Someone needs to check that these blue painted cycling superhighways don't become dangerously slippery when wet or covered with leaves.</span></li></ol><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">Appendices</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">A1 </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">a  Suggestions</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold"> (not legislation) for cyclists</span></p><ol type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 32pt; padding-left:4pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">Don't crawl up the inside of long vehicles</span></li><li style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 32pt; padding-left:4pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">Fit you</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">r bike with a mirror</span></li><li style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 32pt; padding-left:4pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">Wear bright &amp; reflective gear.</span></li><li style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 32pt; padding-left:4pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">Helmets probably don't help much. Maybe a bit.</span></li><li style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 32pt; padding-left:4pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">Avoid rural A roads if you can.</span></li><li style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 32pt; padding-left:4pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">The AA's recommendations are pretty sensible (http://www.theaa.com/motoring_advice/safety/cyclists-and-drivers-sharing-the-ro</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">ad.html)</span></li></ol><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">A1 b Suggestions for drivers</span></p><ol type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 32pt; padding-left:4pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">So what if he doesn't look great in </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">lycra</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">.</span></li><li style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 32pt; padding-left:4pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">Treat cyclists as a normal part of road traffic.</span></li><li style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 32pt; padding-left:4pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">Don't complain about cyclists breaking the law by jumping red lights if you ignore speed limits or use a mobile while drivin</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">g.</span></li><li style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 32pt; padding-left:4pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">If you drive like a loony you probably won't arrive much earlier</span></li><li style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 32pt; padding-left:4pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">The AA's recommendations for drivers </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">( </span><a href="http://www.theaa.com/motoring_advice/safety/cyclists-and-drivers-sharing-the-road.html"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">http://www.theaa.com/motoring_advice/safety/cyclist</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">s-and-drivers-sharing-the-road.html</span></a><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">) are pretty sensible too.</span></li></ol><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">A1 c Suggestion for everyone</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; text-indent:-18pt"><span style="font-family:OpenSymbol; font-size:12pt">•</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">Common courtesy.</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">A2. A note of concern</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">Cycling is cheap. And long may it remain so. This means however that the government has little incentive to promote it </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">as it makes little or no money out of it. My concern is that, at the end of the day, the government will be about as keen as to promote cycling as they have been to take effective steps to discourage irresponsible drinking. The amount of tax that goes to t</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">he Treasury will probably weigh more heavily with the Government than the nation's health or well-being. This is not a party political matter; the previous government was no better. I am sure that there are a lot of people in government who would be only t</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">oo glad if Britain follows the predictions of the "National Transport Model" and the "Cycling Revolution" just never happens.</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-style:italic">December 2013</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><a name="_GoBack"></a><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p></div></body></html>